Class IEEEremainder

              org.apache.pig.piggybank.evaluation.math.IEEEremainder

public class IEEEremainder
extends DoubleDoubleBase

math.IEEEremainder implements a binding to the Java function Math.IEEEremainder(double,double). Given a tuple with two data atom it Returns the remainder operation on two arguments as prescribed by the IEEE 754 standard.

Parameters:
value - Tuple containing two Double.
Return Value:
Double
Return Schema:
IEEEremainder_inputSchema
Example:
register math.jar;
A = load 'mydata' using PigStorage() as ( float1 );
B = foreach A generate float1, math.IEEEremainder(float1);

Author:
ajay garg
See Also:
Math.IEEEremainder(double,double),
